com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.jsom.api
Interface ModifierList

All Superinterfaces:
JSOM
public interface ModifierList
extends JSOM

This JSOM represents a list of modifiers including annotations.

The modifiers themselves are represented by constants defined by this class. A specialty here are annotations. Annotations may occur everywhere modifiers can occur. For the cases were a modifier list contains annotations (as a matter of fact a modifier list can simply contain one annotation but nothing else) the list contains a special modifier constant for each annotation. This means from the point of view of a modifier list an annotation is nothing else then a certain modifier. However, because annotations are a little bit more complex than modifiers (which are simply keywords) there are also some methods to receive the appropriate Annotation objects.

Author:
Dieter Habelitz

getAnnotations

java.util.List<Annotation> getAnnotations(java.util.List<Annotation> pList)
Returns a list of all Annotation objects that exist within the modifier list.

Parameters:
pList - If this argument isn't null the Annotation objects will be added to this list and this list object will be returned. Otherwise a new list will be created for the result.
Returns:
A list of all Annotation objects. If there are no annotations null will be returned, even if the argument pList isn't null.

getModifiers

java.util.List<ModifierList.Modifier> getModifiers()
Returns a list of the modifiers, represented by appropriate ModifierList.Modifier constants, that belong to the modifier list.

Calling this method equals an getModifiers(null) call.

Returns:
A list of the modifiers that belong to the modifier list. If the modifier list is empty, i.e. if there is neither a modifier nor an annotation, null will be returned.
See Also:

isLocalModifierList

boolean isLocalModifierList()
Tells if this represents a local modifier list, i.e. the modifier list of a local variable, of a parameter from a formal parameter list, etc.

Local modifier lists can only contain the modifier final and annotations whereby annotations my occur before and/or after the final keyword.

Returns:
true if this represents a local modifier list.
